Title: As Good As My Word
Description: Find Ranger Heo Do-yun's previous associates. Once found, let them know Heo Do-yun is still alive.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I had the "good fortune" to be off scouting when the Corrupted struck.  \n\nI was cut off from the others, but I was able to track them here. If we don't find them soon, I fear they may fall to Corruption.
InProgressResponse: Please look for any surviving rangers. It would be heartening to know I wasn't the only survivor, this time.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You have the look of someone who has good news! I take it others survived the attack?

Title: Mapping The Edge Of Despair
Description: Find the best locations to map out enemy camps in northern Great Cleave. Then bring your notes back to Ranger Heo Do-yun.
PlayerPrompt: "Is that why you are still here?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes. I was sent to map the supply lines of the Corrupted. With you here, we could cover more ground. \n\nI scouted out several promising locations, but I didn't have time to make maps, not before the bastion was destroyed.
InProgressResponse: We need accurate maps if we are to track what the Corrupted are up to. Each piece of new information brings us closer to victory!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You, my friend, are an extremely competent mapmaker. I know it couldn't have been easy to write in the cold, but this linework is excellent!\n\nNow let me compare these to our older maps.

Title: Picking Up The Pieces
Description: Recover weapons and armor from Ranger Heo Do-yun's fallen companions. Recover Mardea's Shield, Hanu's Spear, Topalian's Helm, and Kaipo's Axe.
PlayerPrompt: "How do you plan on honoring them?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: When we build a new bastion, I plan on putting their prized weapons and armor on display so that we never forget their sacrifices. \n\nEach of them left something behind. Until now, I haven't had the time to recover them.
InProgressResponse: Their warrior spirits will live on forever, but those of us who didn't fall would be reminded about their strength and courage if we had something to remember them by.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Mardea's Shield, as good at absorbing blows as she was hardship. Hanu's quick wit, as sharp as the spear she fought with. \n\nTopalian's Helm, as bright as their personality. And Kaipo's Axe, as large as his generosity.

Title: The Balemaw Beast
Description: Find the notorious Balemaw Beast which has been preying on travelers in the region.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The Balemaw Beast is taller than a person and covered in fur! It has glowing eyes that pierce through the snow and claws as long as daggers. \n\nIt jumps out from behind the trees and vanishes into the woods just as quickly.
InProgressResponse: Have you discovered any clues to the whereabouts of the Balemaw Beast?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: From your expression you have discovered somethingâ€¦ Please let it not be another body. \n\nTell me truthfully, I can handle the worst.

Title: Wolves Of Winter
Description: Track the beasts that have been attacking travelers to their lair and defeat them.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The color of the eyes, along with their ability to manipulate ice, leads me to believe that these creatures aren't natural. \n\nWe can't allow them to make a home here in Great Cleave!
InProgressResponse: Have you checked the nearby ice caves? What about the ones farther away? We have to be sure they aren't spreading.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You look like you've been in quite a fight. Was it with the Yeti? Have you banished it?

Title: The Beast Returns
Description: The Balemaw Beast struck again! Track the beast up Mangled Heights and defeat it!
PlayerPrompt: "Do I need to check on Bob again?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It wouldn't hurt. Though I can't imagine Bob has a hand in this, unless we were vastly mistaken about the nature of his character. \n\nHe seemed harmless. Misguided and foolish, but harmless.
InProgressResponse: These are dark days indeed if such beasts wander the land. \n\nI had thought we had taken care of the Balemaw Beast last time, but it seems we were mistaken.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Has it been taken care of?  Has the beast been destroyed?

Title: A Spot Of Luxury
Description: Gather beautiful Spotted Pelts from Bobcats to add to Rue Horne's collection.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I could tell you were one with a fine eye for fashion. Really, your outfit, superb! I couldn't design something better myself.
InProgressResponse: I must have those spotted pelts! Do hurry back soon!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You found me, good! With you helping to procure the bobcat pelts, I felt I had to scout out what I simple needed to collect next. But first, let's take a look at those pelts.

Title: Fabulous Furs
Description: Gather fantastically colored pelts from local cougars and elk to add to Rue Horne's collection.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: More than unusual, they are extremely profitable! Those hues will mean I save a fortune on dyes! \n\nThe stripes are quite striking too. I simply must add them to my collection.
InProgressResponse: Those colors! They make me weak just thinking about them! I must have them!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Oh. My. They are even better in person than from afar. Oh, and so soft. So supple. \n\nEveryone will be clamoring to wear these, and it's all possible because of you.

Title: Pure Delight
Description: Gather brilliant Pure White Pelts from wolves to add to Rue Horne's collection.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Your concern is touching. But trust me, anyone buying pure white pelts are not worried about how to keep them clean! \n\nI simply must have them!
InProgressResponse: Those pelts are a blank slate just waiting to be gobbled up by fashion. Do be hasty in bringing them back!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Oh, what a wonder! Imagine enfolding yourself in these furs! Why, you'd sink into them and give up wearing anything else. \n\nSuch fine work, it's like you were born to be in fashion.

Title: White As Bone
Description: Collect Ancient Ivory for Valta so she can add it to a poppet.
PlayerPrompt: "But I have seen no children here."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I have not seen children either, but I have listened long to tales older than this island. And I am certain there is a way. \n\nAll I need are some components to place into a poppet.
InProgressResponse: I need bones of the Ancients to make this work.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: These bones, so old, and yet they have not faded away. Something makes these Ancient bones special. Something I hope will imbue this spell with longevity and strength.

Title: Red As Blood
Description: Collect blood red Firebright Rubies from the mine for Valta so she can add them to a poppet.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I tried dyes before, sadly they all failed. This time I shall try rubies, blood red in color. They donâ€™t fade with time, always staying bright. \n\nThereâ€™s a mine not far from here where rubies can be collected.
InProgressResponse: I need bright shining rubies to make this spell work. \n\nI tried blood and dye before, but those didn't last long enough.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: How deep their color, like blood that has been caught and frozen in time. \n\nSee how they catch the light? These are perfect to capture the spirit of survival anyone on Aeternum needs.

Title: Black As Ebony
Description: Collect night black pieces of Charred Ebony for Valta so she can add them to a poppet.
PlayerPrompt: "You can't give up now, I'm sure we can find some."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I have heard rumors that someone brought ebony furniture to one of the forts. You could search there and see what you could find. \n\nI fear the worst, as the rumors also told of the forts being overrun.
InProgressResponse: All I require now are charred pieces of ebony. Soon, my child soon, you shall know peace in my arms.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Perfect, perfect. The bones are inside, with rubies for the heart and eyes, and charred pieces of ebony to hold it all together. \n\nThe poppet is complete!

Title: An Offering For Offspring
Description: Travel to the Wishing Tree and leave the Poppet as an offering so that Valta may one day have a child of her own.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I don't know. What I do know is that none of my previous offerings worked. The poppet of snow and blood and ash barely lasted a day before it melted away. \n\nThe poppet of paper and dye didn't fare much better.
InProgressResponse: Please take the poppet to the Wishing Tree. I can hear the voice of my child even now.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Something is different, I can feel it. \n\nThe air has a hint of warmth to it. The wind holds fewer sighs.

Title: Perfect Piroshkis
Description: Gather Dried Dill, Crumbly Aged Cheese, and Tenderized Meat for Aksinya.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Tell me about it! Why, I haven't had new deliveries in quite some time, and it shows.  \n\nI've got plenty of potatoes, but there are only so many ways you can cook them.
InProgressResponse: What I wouldn't give for some spices, cheeseâ€¦ anything to brighten the potatoes and onions I already have on hand.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You did it! I almost can't believe it, it's been so long since I've seen something other than potatoes to eat! \n\nTell me I'm not dreaming.

Title: To Warm The Soul Warden
Description: Bring Piping-Hot Piroshkis to Soulwarden Pedro Carrillo at Warden's Rise before they get cold!
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I've already made food for everyone stationed here, and I want to spread the bounty around.  \n\nI can't imagine the kind of swill they are eating over there, the poor dears.
InProgressResponse: Off with you! You don't want those piroshkis to get cold, do you? \n\nWithout being able to use the Spirit Shrine, you'll need to get a move on!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: That smells wonderful! Marvelous! I haven't had any food that smelled this good forâ€¦ I don't remember how long! What's the occasion?

Title: Prime Resolve
Description: Gather supplies for Ranger Law to make Prime Resolve.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Here in Aeternum, where doom haunts our every move, we must hang on to the things that make us feel alive.\n\nTo that end, there is a legend we tell in Great Cleave that warms our hearts.
